For the purpose of taxation, the State is divided into four districts, viz.: 



	(a)	The city and county of Honolulu, to be called the first district; 
	(b)	The counties of Maui and Kalawao, to be called the second district; 
	(c)	The county of Hawaii, to be called the third district; 
	(d)	The county of Kauai, to be called the fourth district. [L 1932 2d, c 40, §2; RL 1935, §1901; RL 1945, §5102; RL 1955, §115-2; am L 1967, c 37, §1; HRS ]




